==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English [[directen]], from Latin [[directus|dīrectus]], [[derectus|dērectus]], past participle of [[dirigere|dīrigere]], [[derigere|dērigere]] "to direct, arrange", from [[dis-]] + [[regere]] "to guide, direct".

